img_caption: God is moving!! The past couple days have been incredible. It's a small world and there have been moments where God is the only one that could make these occurrences happen. Just on Tuesday Night our flight from Munich to Paris got cancelled we were able to talk with European customer service and get on the next flight just an hour later on standby. We landed safely in Paris and took a bus to the station nearest our Hostel. We ended up running into a 25 year old man named Carlos who was from Yukatan and he was as lost as we were in such a new city. His friend he was meeting in Paris was a day late and he didn't have a place to stay. He ended up coming with us to our Hostel which was full and the owner of the hostel allowed him to sleep on the floor in our room. All day the next day he came with us to the Eiffel Tower and we shared stories we laughed and we didn't care about the language barrier or our life circumstances. For that moment we were One. He left that night as family and left us with a saying  Mi Casa es tu Casa   My house is your house . Later that night a young man named Anurug got to the Hostel but it was full and he pleaded for a spot the owner allowed him. I just started talking to him in the lobby and we conversed and talked about traveling experiences. He was from Tanzania. He ended up being by himself in Paris and We invited him to come along with us the next day to the Palace of Versailles. It was a beautiful day and again we shared stories and culture. He invited us to Tanzania and will continue to be a friend for a life time. It is these moments that we put differences aside to just be as God calls us to be One.

img_caption: just because you're alone right now doesn't mean you're undateable. just because that pretty girl won't smile back at you doesn't mean you're undesirable. just because you haven't kissed a boy doesn't mean you're unattractive. stop blaming yourself for these things. love is one of those weird cosmic things that is simply beyond your control. you can try as hard as you like but really it'll only come to you when the time is right. stop thinking there is something wrong with YOU. there is absolutely NOTHING wrong with you. you are insanely attractive highly intelligent hella sweet and mad funny. stop discounting that. you are worth so so so much! i don't want you to forget that just because you haven't found  the one  yet.  the one  could be across the world at some random cafÃ:: reading your favorite book and drinking those chai lattes you love so much.  the one  could even be right next to you hoping you feel the same way as they feel about you.  the one  could be feeling just as alone as you do right now wishing they could just meet you already. and we'll never know where  the one  is at this moment and yeah that fucking sucks! hardcore!! but don't fret my dear. everything will fall into place soon. in the meantime fall in love with the wrong people. make mistakes. discover yourself. love yourself. img_caption: What does UGA mean to me?  Home. I moved to the Georgia about six years ago from Washington state halfway through my high school career. Although my new school was a wonderful place I found it difficult to fit in and truly be myself. So when I came to UGA I was looking for somewhere I could grow. Somewhere to find a community. I am excited that I get to constantly enjoy what I have chosen to study. How lucky am I that my mind is blown every day I go to class! I have received such a rounded education here-I am confident in my abilities to contribute and give back to the communities that have given so much to me.  In the end the organization endorsements don't matter. The campaigning the stickers the buttons the profile pictures all of those are temporary. They will fade with time. However the endless amount of support and love that I have felt is not. No matter the outcome of this week I will always remember this feeling. And no matter who is crowned I know that they will be absolutely deserving because this Court is full of incredible individuals who will all change the world in their own ways!
